Quick and dirty clone of fvid[1], with C and shell scripts.

# Building

$ make

# Installation

No.

# Usage

data2ff, ff2data - convert between data and farbfeld image, each black and white
	pixel representing a single bit.
ff2png, png2ff - convert between farbfeld image and png.
encode.sh, decode.sh - convert between data and video.

$ ./encode.sh input_data.file output_video.mp4
$ ./decode.sh input_video.mp4 output_data.file


util.c, util.h, ff2png.c and png2ff.c are originally from farbfeld[2] distribution.

[1] https://github.com/AlfredoSequeida/fvid
[2] http://tools.suckless.org/farbfeld/
